#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: var-topdef-shared
---

# top-level var mutated from def bodies (shared cell)

Regression for BUGS.md `v2-topvar-def-split-cell`: a top-level `var` referenced
from def bodies must be ONE shared cell. The v2 bridge bound the entry-block
occurrences to a Let-local cell while def bodies reached an auto-created
`Global("@name")` — two different cells, so mutations from defs silently
vanished (busi's `def saveLocal(t) = localCell = t` persistence pattern).

```scalascript
var cell = ""
var count = 0

def saveText(t: String): Unit = cell = t

def bump(): Unit =
  count = count + 1
  cell = cell + "!"

saveText("one")
println(cell)
bump()
bump()
println(cell)
println(count)
```
